@node "Intro" "Introduktion"
                               @{b}INTRODUCTION@{ub}

The GlossTask is the programme which you do your glossary
home work with. It can test you from one language to another.
The programme is managed by mouse and very easy to use.
Of course you can save your vocabulary list for use at another
occasion.
  
This is a DEMO-version of the registered version of GlossTask.
In this version some features are missing, for instance the
ability to save your vocabulary list.

If you @{"register" link "regi" 0} you will get the registered
complete version of the GlossTask.

@endnode

@node "requi" "Requirements"

GlossTask require Kickstart 2.04 and Workbench 2.0 or higher.

@endnode

@node "Install" "Installation"
                          @{b}INSTALLATION@{ub}

EVERYONE HAS TO INSTALL GlossTask BEFORE USE!

Harddisk-users:
Click the installer-script, Install_to_harddisk.

Floppy only users:
Click the installer-script, Install_floppyonly_users.

@endnode

@node "Starta" "To start the GlossTask"
			@{b}TO START THE GlossTask@{ub}

From Workbench:
	Doubleclick on the GlossTask icon in Workbench.

From CLI
	Type in "GlossTask" at the CLI-prompt, and press ENTER!

@endnode

@node "MaGl" "Att mata in glosorna"
		    @{b}TO REGISTER THE VOCABLES@{ub}

Click, with left mousebutton, in the upper vocable box and type in
the foreign word. End by pressing ENTER. The cursor will then
jump down to the lower vocable box, where you type in the translation.
End by pressing ENTER. @{"Increase the Voc.nr" link "GlSt" 0}. Then
click in the upper vocable box again. But there is an easier way. You
don't have to do this for every vocable, just use the
@{"Automated voc.nr.increaser" link "Auto" 0}. When you have registered
all your vocables you set this feature to off.

         @{"To change vocabulary test languages" link "förspr" 0}
@endnode

@node "GlSt" "Att stega sig framĺt och bakĺt.."
        @{b}TO GO FORWARD AND BACKWARD AMONG THE VOCABLES@{ub}

Every vocable has been assigned a voc.nr. By using the arrow buttons,
which are above the upper vocable box, you can go forward and backward
among your vocables. The little arrows increase or decrease by one, and
the long arrows increase or decrease by ten. In the box between the arrows
the current voc.nr is shown, and in the box on the right side of the
buttons the number of already registered vocables is shown.

@endnode

@node "Knappar" "Buttons"
                           @{b}BUTTONS@{ub}

          @{"IN" link "Infog" 0} Insert a vocable
          @{"ER" link "Rad" 0} Erase a vocable
          @{"CLEAR" link "Rensa" 0} Clear the whole vocabulary list
          @{"L" link "Ladda" 0} Load a vocabulary list
          @{"S" link "Spara" 0} Save a vocabulary list
          @{"S.." link "Sparany" 0} Save a new vocabulary list
          @{"PRINT" link "Utskrift" 0} Print out your vocabulary list
          @{"TEST" link "Träna" 0} Vocabulary test
          @{"SEEK" link "Sök" 0} Seek for a word 
          @{"QUIT TEST" link "Avsltr" 0} Quit the test
          @{"RIGHT ANS" link "Rätts" 0} Get the right answer

@{b}Multi-choice-buttons:@{ub}

          @{"Foreign lang/English" link "FöSä" 0} Kind of test
          @{"Random/Start/End/Missed/Mouse" link "FöOr" 0} In which order?

@{b}Check-box-buttons:@{ub}

          @{" " link "Prata" 0} Talk
          @{" " link "Auto" 0} Auto


@endnode

@node "Infog" "To insert a vocable"
	           @{b}TO INSERT A VOCABLE@{ub}
 
If you want to insert a vocable between two voc.nrs, you set the voc.nr
to the right voc.nr and click att the "IN" button. An empty voc.nr will
be created, and you type in the vocable in the usual way.

                    @{"To register vocables" link "MaGl" 0}

   ******** This feature don't work in the DEMO-version ********

@endnode

@node "rad" "To erase a vocable"
                @{b}TO ERASE A VOCABLE@{ub}

If you want to erase a vocable you use the arrow buttons to go
to the right voc.nr and click the "ER" button.

ATTENTION! You can't get back vocables which you have deleted!


               @{"Clear the whole vocabulary list" link "Rensa" 0}

@endnode

@node "Rensa" "Clear the whole vocabulary list"
                 @{b}CLEAR THE WHOLE VOCABULARY LIST@{ub}

If you want to clear the whole vocabulary list you click the "CLEAR"
button. 

ATTENTION! You can't get back vocables which you have deleted!

                 @{"Erase a vocable" link "rad" 0}

   ******** This feature don't work in the DEMO-version ********

@endnode

@node "Ladda" "Load a vocabulary list"

                @{b}TO LOAD A VOCABULARY LIST@{ub}

If you want to load a vocabulary list click the "L"-button. A file-
requester will appear. Choose the file you want to load, by clicking
on it, so will be highlighted, then click the "OK"-button.

Is it time for a big test, you probably want to join all the vocabulary
list to one. You do just that in the following way:

1. Click the "L"- button and click on the first vocabulary list. 
2. Click on the other vocabulary lists, while you are holding the
SHIFT-key down.
3. Click on the OK-button. All the highlighted will then be loaded, one after
another. 
4. @{"Save" link "Sparany" 0} the new vocabulary list under a new name.

@endnode

@node "Spara" "To save a vocabulary list"
		@{b}TO SAVE CHANGES IN A VOCABULARY LIST@{ub}

When you have loaded a vocabulary list and the altered it, you can
save it directly under the same name by just clicking the "S"-button.
                  @{"Save a new vocabulary list" link "Sparany" 0}.

   ******** This feature don't work in the DEMO-version ********

@endnode

@node "Sparany" "Save as.."
              @{b}TO SAVE A NEW VOCABULARY LIST (Save as..)@{ub}

If you want to save a new vocabulary list, click the "S.."-button. A file-
requester will appear. Name the the vocabulary list as anything, and type it
in the filerequester box. End by pressing ENTER or by clicking on the "OK"-button.

The filename will be shown in the filename box at upper part of the screen.

   ******** This feature don't work in the DEMO-version ********

@endnode

@node "Utskrift" "Print out"
         @{b}TO PRINT OUT THE VOCABULARY LIST TO A PRINTER@{ub}

Click on the "PRINT"-button. If everything is okey, the printer settings
window now will appear. The GlossTask uses the printer settings which
you have done in Preferences in Workbench, but some setting have to be
done in this window.

                      @{b}BUTTONS@{ub}

@{"Print Quality" link "utskval" 0}
@{"Margin" link "marginal" 0}
@{"Header" link "Rubrikin" 0}
@{"Vocables" link "Glosan" 0}
@{"Char(acter)s per line" link "Tkprad" 0}
@{"Density" link "Täthet" 0}
@{"Font" link "Typsnitt" 0}

@{b}Print@{ub} Print out the vocabulary list
@{"Save" link "Sparins" 0}   Save the settings
@{b}Quit@{ub}  Go back to main screen

@endnode

@node "utskval" "Print Quality"
               @{b}PRINT QUALITY@{ub}

Select whether you want to print out with NLQ or not.

@endnode

@node "marginal" "Margin settings"
             @{b}MARGIN SETTINGS@{ub}

Choose how many characters from left, and how many lines from
the top, which you want the printout to appear.

@endnode

@node "rubrikin" "Header text"
               @{b}HEADER TEXT@{ub}

Select whether you want the filename or a optional text to appear at the top of the
paper. The text you type in the box beside.
@endnode

@node "glosan" "Which vocables will be outprinted?"
         @{b}WHICH VOCABLES WILL BE OUTPRINTED?@{ub}

Select between "all vocables" or "vocables within a range".

@endnode

@node "Tkprad" "Char(acter)s per line"
           @{b}NUMBER OF CHARACTERS PER LINE@{ub}

Decide how many character it should be per line in the
vocabl and in the translation. Time for testing :-)  

@endnode

@node "täthet" "To use smaller fonts"
            @{b}DENSITY( USE SMALLER FONTS )@{ub}

Mark these boxes if you want to use the smallest of the in-build
fonts of the printer.

@endnode

@node "typsnitt" "Chose font"
                  @{b}TYPSNITT@{ub}

Decide which in-build printer font you want to use, by writing
the printer code for the font you want to use. The printer code
is to begin with ESC. For example: ESC h65rhsT

The font should be fixed, proportional font don't give that good
results.

   ******** This feature don't work in the DEMO-version ********
   The current font of the printer will be used.

@endnode

@node "sparins" "Save the settings"
             @{b}SAVE THE SETTINGS@{ub}

Save the settings to the S: directory on your startup-disc or
partition.

   ******** This feature don't work in the DEMO-version ********

@endnode

@node "Träna" "Vocabulary test"
                     @{b}VOCABULARY TEST@{ub}
 
The computer can check your vocable spelling. Click on the "TEST"-
button.

                      @{"In which order?" link "FöOr" 0}

                       @{"Kind of test" link "FöSä" 0 }

              @{"To make the Amiga speak" link "Prata" 0}

                   @{"To stop a vocabulary test" link "Avsltr" 0}

                  @{"To get the right answer" link "rätts" 0}

                 @{"To change vocabulary test languages" link "förspr" 0}
@endnode

@node "FöOr" "In which order?"
                    @{b}IN WHICH ORDER?@{ub}

You can choose between five different test orders:
"Random", "Start", "End", "Missed" and "Mouse" by clicking the button
beside "TEST" tills the right order is shown.

@{"Random" link "Vanligt förhör" 0} the vocables are chosen by random (DEFAULT).
@{"Start" link "Vanligt förhör" 0} test in forward order.
@{"End" link "Vanligt förhör" 0} test in backward order.
@{"Missed" link "Missade" 0} test on missed vocables
@{"Mouse" link "musj" 0} play the Mousehunt while you are do

@endnode
@node "FöSä" "Kind of test"
                    @{b}KIND OF TEST@{ub}

You can choose between to have a test to "Foreign lang" or to
your mother-tongue, by clicking the button till the right language
is shown.

"Foreign lang" = the programme will ask you what the word is in the
foreign language. (DEFAULT).
"Mother-tongue" = the programme will ask you what the word is in your
mother-tongue. 

@endnode

@node "Prata" "Talk"
             @{b}TO MAKE THE AMIGA SPEAK@{ub}

Amiga can say the question through your Amiga Talksynthes.
Mark the checkbox for "Talk".

@endnode

@node "Avsltr" "To stop the vocabulary test"
              @{b}TO STOP THE VOCABULARY TEST@{ub}

Click the "QUIT TEST"-button to stop the vocabulary test.

   ******** This feature don't work in the DEMO-version ********

@endnode

@node "rätts" "Fĺ reda pĺ rätt svar"
           @{b}TO GET THE RIGHT ANSWER@{ub}

If you absolutely can't answer a question, you can get the right
answer by clicking on the "RIGHT ANS"-button. The right answer
will then be shown in the lower part of the screen.

   ******** This feature don't work in the DEMO-version ********

@endnode
@node "ÄnGl" "Ändra glosa"
           @{b}TO ALTER AN ALREADY REGISTERED VOCABLE@{ub}

Click with the left mousebutton where the altering is to begin,
and do your changes.

@endnode

@node "Glist" "Gloslistefönstret"
                  @{b}THE VOCABULARY LIST WINDOW@{ub}

In lower part of the screen you can find the vocabulary list window.
You can go backward and forward among yor vocables by clicking on
the arrow-buttons, or by using the proportional gadget.

If you click on a vocable in the vocabulary list window, this vocable
will appear in the upper and lower vocable boxes.
 
@endnode

@node "Vanligt förhör" "Testing options"

The computer will ask you what the vocable is in the foreign language,
and you answer in the lower vocable box. The translation to the
vocable the computer ask you for is in the upper vocable box.
If your answer is wrong the question will be asked tills you answer
right. If you absolutely can't find out the right word you click on
the @("RIGHT ANS" link "Rätts" 0}-button to get the right answer.

@endnode

@node "Sök"
                     @{b}TO SEEK FOR A VOCABLE@{ub}

Click on the "SEEK"-button and type in the word you wil search for in the
lower vocable box. And press ENTER. The searching will start from
the current voc.nr.

@endnode

@node "Missade" "Förhör pĺ missade glosor"
               @{b}TEST ON MISSED VOCABLES@{ub}

This feature is good if you want train more on the vocables
which you have answered wrongly in the previous test. Only
vocables which have been wrongly answered will be asked with
this feature on.

The computer will ask you what the vocable is in the foreign language,
and you answer in the lower vocable box. The translation to the
vocable the computer ask you for is in the upper vocable box.
If your answer is wrong the question will be asked tills you answer
right. If you absolutely can't find out the right word you click on
the @("RIGHT ANS" link "Rätts" 0}-button to get the right answer.

@endnode

@node "Musj" "Musjakten"
                        @{b}THE MOUSEHUNT@{ub}

This is a game, in which you should answer right on vocable questions
in the shortest possible time.

Nine boxes, which contain randomly chosen vocables, will appear on the
screen. Click in the box, where you find the right translation, to the
vocable which stands in the box in upper part of the screen.In lower
 part of the screen you will find the time.

ATTENTION! You must have atleast ten vocables, in the vocabulary list,
for this feature to work.

   ******** This feature don't work in the DEMO-version ********

@endnode

@node "stat" "The status box"
                     @{b}THE STATUS BOX@{ub}

In the status box the programme will tell you what is going on.
(erasing, saving, loading, printing). 

@endnode

