@node "Auto" "Automatic voc.nr-increaser"
            @{b}TO USE THE AUTOMATIC VOC.NR-INCREASER@{ub}

By mark the checkbox "Auto" between the two vocable boxes, the feature
is activated. Now you don't have to increase the voc.nr manually.

@endnode

@node "instäl" "The main settings progaramme"

                     @{b}MAIN SETTINGS@{ub}

With the programme Glos_settings you can alter some main
settings.

@{b}'LOAD'@{ub} Load a settings file. The default settings file GlossTask.config
is loaded automatically every time the programme is started.

@{b}'SAVE'@{ub} Save the settings. They should be save in the S: directory on
your startup-disc or partition.

@{b}'Maximum number of vocables'@{ub}. How many vocables do you want to be able
to have at the same time? The more vocables, the more memory is required.

   ******** This feature don't work in the DEMO-version ********
   Maximum number of vocables i allways 80 pcs.

@{b}'Maximum number of char(acter)s per vocable'@{ub}. Hpw many characters do
you need per vocable?
The more characters, the more memory is required. This setting is good
if you have to register long sentences.

   ******** This feature don't work in the DEMO-version ********
   Maximum number of characters per vocable is allways 72 pcs.

@{b}'Talk feature available'@{ub}. Here you can choose if you want
to be able to use the talkfeature. To be able to use it you must
have Narrator.device and Translator.library installed. These files
don't go with Workbench 3.0+ disks, but if you have an old WB1.3
disk you can copy these files over to your WB3.0+. If this checkbox
is marked and these files are not installed, a requester will
appear every time you start GlossTask, telling you that
the talk feature won't work.

@{b}'Vocabulary list path (volume)'@{ub}. Here you tell GlossTask
where to search for vocabulary lists.

@{b}'Mother-tongue'@{ub}. Here you tell GlossTask, which language
which is your mother-tongue. This language will be in the box above
the lower vocable box.

@endnode

@node "förspr" "To change the test languages"

            @{b}TO CHANGE THE VOCABULARY TEST LANGUAGES@{ub}

Type in language of your choice, which you want to have tests between,
in the little boxes above the vocable boxes.

@endnode

@node "felm" "Error messages"
                  @{b}ERROR MESSAGES@{ub}

@{b}'Could not open S:GlossTask.config'@{ub} GlossTask could not open
the settings file GlossTask.config, which is to be in the S: directory
on your startup-disk or partition.
The GlossTask has to be installed before use! Even Amiga owners without
hard disk have to do it. If you have a hard disk start the installer-script,
Install_to_Harddisk. If you don't have any you start the installer-script,
Install_floppyonly_users.

@endnode

